    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "More evidence, from a large-scale study in China, that using AI hurts learning if it undermines mental effort. When homework time drops due to AI use, so do test scores.\n\nAcross studies, a theme: AI tutoring in support of classes is good, using AI to \"help\" with homework is bad. https://t.co/QO67l4Scr4",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2067988324984217626",
    "time": "2026-06-19 23:10",
    "created_at": "Fri Jun 19 15:10:12 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2067988324984217626",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "The instinct of students is often to use AI to help with homework, even if they are not trying to cheat. And because off-the-shelf chatbots are a helpful assistant, rather than a tutor, they give you the answer and undermine learning.\n\nPaper: https://t.co/wBAh6iUukz",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2067989839740309698",
    "time": "2026-06-19 23:16",
    "created_at": "Fri Jun 19 15:16:13 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2067989839740309698",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "I talk about the research on when AI undermines, versus supporting, thinking and learning here: https://t.co/NqWO8wyVG8",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
